declarations.comments:
If the node type is document fragment, element, text, processing
instruction, or comment this is the node's data, or null in all other
cases.
declarations.title: textContent

declarations.comments:
If the node type is document fragment, element, text, processing
instruction, or comment this allows the node's data to be changed, or has
no effect in all other cases.
declarations.title: setTextContent

declarations.comments:
If the node type is text, comment, or processing instruction this allows
the node's data to be changed, or has no effect in all other cases.
declarations.title: setNodeValue

declarations.comments:
Uses the first node as a replacement for the second node in the children
of the third node.
declarations.title: replaceChild

declarations.comments: Removes the first node from the children of the second node.
declarations.title: removeChild

declarations.comments: The previous sibling node, or null if there is no previous sibling.
declarations.title: previousSibling

declarations.comments: The parent node of the node.
declarations.title: parentNode

declarations.comments: The parent element of the node.
declarations.title: parentElement

declarations.comments:
The document the node belongs to, unless the node is a document in which
case the value is null.
declarations.title: ownerDocument

declarations.comments:
Removes empty text nodes and then combines any remaining text nodes that
are contiguous.
declarations.title: normalize

declarations.comments:
If the node type is text, comment, or processing instruction this is the
node's data, or null in all other cases.
declarations.title: nodeValue

declarations.comments: The numeric value for the type of a node.
declarations.title: nodeTypeIndex

declarations.comments: The type of a node.
declarations.title: nodeType

declarations.comments:
For elements this is the tag name, for document types this is the doctype
name, for processing instructions this is the target, for all other nodes
it is a string like `"#text"`, `"#comment", etc. depending on the node
type.
declarations.title: nodeName

declarations.comments: The next sibling node, or null if there is no next sibling.
declarations.title: nextSibling

declarations.comments: The last child of the node, or null if the node has no children.
declarations.title: lastChild

declarations.comments: Checks whether two nodes are equivalent.
declarations.title: isEqualNode

declarations.comments: Inserts the first node before the second as a child of the third node.
declarations.title: insertBefore

declarations.comments: Indicates whether the node has any child nodes.
declarations.title: hasChildNodes

declarations.comments: The first child of the node, or null if the node has no children.
declarations.title: firstChild

declarations.comments: Checks whether the second node is contained within the first
declarations.title: contains

declarations.comments: Compares the position of two nodes in the document.
declarations.title: compareDocumentPositionBits

declarations.comments: The children of the node.
declarations.title: childNodes

declarations.comments: The node's base URL.
declarations.title: baseURI

declarations.comments: Appends the first node to the child node list of the second node.
declarations.title: appendChild

declarations.comments: A class for subtypes of `Element`.
declarations.title: IsElement

declarations.comments: A class for subtypes of `Event`.
declarations.title: IsEvent

declarations.comments: The event type.
declarations.title: type_

declarations.comments: The element that was the source of the event.
declarations.title: target

declarations.comments: The element that the event listener was added to.
declarations.title: currentTarget

declarations.comments:
Indicates which phase of the event flow that is currently being processed
for the event.
declarations.title: eventPhase

declarations.comments: The integer value for the current event phase.
declarations.title: eventPhaseIndex

declarations.comments:
Prevents the event from bubbling up to futher event listeners. Other event
listeners on the current target will still fire.
declarations.title: stopPropagation

declarations.comments:
Prevents all other listeners for the event from being called. This includes
event listeners added to the current target after the current listener.
declarations.title: stopImmediatePropagation

declarations.comments: Indicates whether the event will bubble up through the DOM or not.
declarations.title: bubbles

declarations.comments: Indicates whether the event can be cancelled.
declarations.title: cancelable

declarations.comments: Cancels the event if it can be cancelled.
declarations.title: preventDefault

declarations.comments: Indicates whether `preventDefault` was called on the event.
declarations.title: defaultPrevented

declarations.comments:
The time in milliseconds between 01/01/1970 and when the event was
dispatched.
declarations.title: timeStamp
